SIMPLE: scornful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scornful
<hw>Scorn"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
scorn or contempt; contemptuous; disdainful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Scornful</qex> of winter's frost and summer's sun.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dart not <qex>scornful</qex> glances from those eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Treated with scorn; exciting scorn.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>scornful</qex> mark of every open eye.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Contemptuous; disdainful; contumelious;
reproachful; insolent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Scorn"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Scorn"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scorny</ent>⟦br⟧
